  "datePublished": "2026-03-05",
  "description": "The greatest common divisor of two integers is the largest positive integer that divides both of them. The GCD of 12 and 18 is 6, because 6 divides both 12 and 18, and no larger number does. The GCD of 15 and 28 is 1 — they share no common factor other than 1, making them coprime. The GCD captures the \u0026ldquo;shared multiplicative structure\u0026rdquo; of two numbers: it is the largest factor they have in common.\n",
